      detailedReview: "I've been on the Search Quality team for 4 years. The layoffs in early 2024 changed everything. Before: people would coast on 20% projects and still get 'Exceeds Expectations.' Now: the perf bar is real. OMAP (the new review system) actually has teeth — I've seen two people on my team get 'Needs Improvement' this cycle, which would've been unheard of 3 years ago.\n\nThe good news: if you're a strong performer, it's never been better. RSU refreshers for top performers are generous — I got a $180K grant this cycle on top of my existing vesting. The food is still free (breakfast, lunch, dinner at MTK campus), the massage chairs still work, and the WLB is still better than 95% of tech companies.\n\nThe Gemini push is everywhere. If your project isn't AI-related, good luck getting headcount or visibility. My team pivoted to integrating LLMs into search ranking and suddenly we're the darlings of the org — we got 4 new headcount approved in a quarter where most teams got zero.\n\nOne thing that hasn't changed: the quality of colleagues. I work with people who literally wrote the textbooks on information retrieval. A casual hallway conversation here is more educational than most conference talks. That intellectual density is Google's real competitive advantage, not the free food.",
