      detailedReview: "GCP is Google's third priority behind Search and YouTube, and it shows in headcount allocation. We're constantly fighting for resources against those orgs. That said, the technical problems are fascinating — building infrastructure that competes with AWS at global scale with different architectural philosophies.\n\nMy TC at Staff (L6) is around $560K: $230K base, $35K bonus, ~$295K in RSUs vesting from grants over the past 3 years. The RSU appreciation has been decent (~30% over 2 years) but nothing like NVIDIA or even Meta's recent run. What keeps me here is the autonomy — I basically set the technical direction for my product area with minimal interference.\n\nBiggest frustration: strategy changes every 18 months. Thomas Kurian has vision but the execution layer keeps pivoting between 'compete head-to-head with AWS' and 'differentiate with AI/ML integration.' We've rewritten our auth layer 3 times in 5 years because the strategy for enterprise vs. developer-first kept flip-flopping.\n\nAt Staff level, the role is 70% influence and 30% code. I write maybe 10 hours of code per week, but I review 40+ CLs (changelists) and write design docs that shape the work of 3 teams. The impact leverage is enormous but it requires strong communication skills — you can't hide behind code at this level.",
