      interviewExperience: "Standard Meta loop: 2 coding (Leetcode medium — one was a tree traversal with memoization, one was an array problem with a sliding window), 1 system design (FE-focused: 'design Instagram Stories with offline support and real-time updates'), 1 behavioral.\n\nThe FE system design round is unique to Meta and is where most backend engineers struggle. They want you to think about: component architecture (how to structure a complex React tree), state management (local vs global, when to use each), performance at scale (virtualized lists, lazy loading, bundle splitting), and real-time synchronization. It's not just 'draw boxes' — they want React-level specifics.\n\nI over-prepared on Leetcode hard and the actual questions were easier than I expected. The system design and behavioral rounds were the real differentiators. For behavioral: have specific stories about shipping under pressure, handling technical disagreements, and learning from failures.",
