      teamCulture: "Reels team is high-energy, high-visibility. Zuck personally reviews our engagement metrics monthly, which adds pressure but also means we get resources when we need them. The IC culture is strong — engineers have real product influence. My suggestion for a new video editing feature went from Slack message to shipped product in 6 weeks.\n\nCode review norms: thorough but fast. Diff reviews are public and anyone can comment. There's healthy debate about technical approaches but it never gets personal. The 'move fast' culture is real but post-efficiency-year it's more 'move fast with quality' than the old 'move fast and break things.'",
