      workLifeBalance: "Better than iOS client teams. 40-43 hrs/week consistently. No WWDC crunch for backend teams — our deadlines are decoupled from the hardware release cycle. On-call is 1 week per 6 weeks, and iCloud backend is mature enough that critical pages are rare (maybe once per rotation).\n\nThe biggest WLB factor is the Cupertino commute. I live in SF and the 45-minute drive each way is my least favorite part of the job. Apple's shuttle service helps but it only runs certain routes.",
