      advice: "Apple backend is a hidden gem for distributed systems engineers. If you love consistency models, replication protocols, and operating at exabyte scale, this is your place. For interviews: study CRDTs, Paxos/Raft, and multi-region data replication patterns. Being able to discuss Apple's specific sync challenges (offline-first, privacy-preserving, cross-device) shows you've done your homework.",
